    "interfaceContracts": [
      "One project-owned filesystem-synchronized ChapterFlowUITests/UpgradeEvidence group compiles every package-owned exact test file without later project-file edits.",
      "Stable data, locale, clock, animation, and OS-dependent chrome boundaries are explicit.",
      "Baselines change only with an explained design/behavior change.",
      "Each feature package closes its own localization/adaptation findings against the shared inventory.",
      "This package owns target-owned Share/Action catalogs, localized copy, visual/accessibility rendering, and deterministic fixtures for capture, signed-out, pending, failure, and committed presentation states.",
      "Each NATIVE-owned extension view declares a target-local transaction-agnostic ExtensionPresentationResultInput with exactly pending, committed, and failure(retryable) presentation outcomes; the type performs no outbox write, durability decision, dismissal, or app opening.",
      "A separate DEBUG/test-only fixture initializer injects ExtensionPresentationResultInput and records stateSource=fixture and transactionClaim=none; production controllers cannot select that initializer or inject fixture state.",
      "The existing production initializer labels and void callback types remain source-compatible until WP-EXT-01, but that legacy path is known-red and fail-closed: Save/Ask never invokes the void capture/completion callback, never enters committed/success or announces success, never dismisses/opens, clears busy state, retains the original payload/note, and presents localized retry/error with Cancel remaining available.",
      "A distinct production result-provider overload accepts ExtensionPresentationResultInput without interpreting transaction authority; WP-EXT-01 exclusively supplies that provider, maps durable writer results, retires both legacy controller call sites, and owns durable-success/failure/dismissal/app-open validation without editing NATIVE views or catalogs.",
      "The touch-target inventory distinguishes verified-compliant, verified-exception, owner-closure-required, and unverified; owner assignment is never compliance, and WP-READER-01 closes reader-toolbar.depth-option and reader-toolbar.tone-option.",
      "The existing scripts/visual/touch_targets.py owns one fail-closed --self-test mode with exactly 20 unique reviewed named cases. Every case executes the same production scanner seam used by --check; the complete registry and executed set must match with matched=20, passed=20, failed=0, skipped=0, and any missing, duplicate, silently unexecuted, altered, skipped, or expectation-drifted case fails. No dedicated test file is added, and reader-toolbar.depth-option and reader-toolbar.tone-option remain WP-READER-01 owner closures.",
      "The paired iOS performance runner exposes one canonical fail-closed CLI using exact main/candidate worktrees and expected HEADs, project/scheme/test, structured budget ID, 30 samples, budget-declared device classes, pinned OS/toolchain/fixture, isolated DerivedData, ordered Hangs/SwiftUI templates, and one retained artifact directory; it builds current-main first, rejects incompatible legacy or mismatched options, retains every sample/xcresult/trace, and never authors or relaxes a budget.",
      "The runner self-test parses and plans complete PERF-READER-PAGINATION and PERF-GRAPH-INTERACTION consumer fixtures, proves their distinct structured semantic joins, and rejects missing, unknown, duplicate, relaxed, or cross-wired budget inputs."
    ]
  },
